title: If The Starks Had Blogs
body:
Sansa:  Most popular blogger in the north. Has several thousand followers. Sets up a lot of go fund me’s to make sure everyone has food and clothes. Also has a private blog where she writes poetry and posts a lot of sewing and baking tutorials.

Arya:  She’s constantly changing her URL and avatar so it’s nearly impossible to tell who she really is. Isn’t on very often but will occasionally log on to trash talk someone. Strangely enough, whenever she names someone on her blog, they’re never heard from again.

Bran:  Has never changed his default settings since he first made his blog. Writes a lot of weirdly existential posts that half the people who follow him find beautiful and haunting and the other half find hilariously meme worthy. No one’s ever quite sure if he’s trolling. If asked to elaborate on one of his vaguely threatening posts, he’ll refuse to comment.

Jon:  Has a secret blog that he and his friends run, posting about his day to day life and adventures at the wall. Gets enormously popular overnight which gets him in trouble with his commander (especially after everything they wrote about him on the blog). Lots of typical bro stuff and complaints about the cold. His most popular posts are always pictures of Ghost though.

summary: what are your top 5 moments featuring meera's A+ big sister skills?
question: what are your top 5 moments featuring meera's A+ big sister skills?
answer:
Okay so I’m having trouble keeping track of stuff + I’m too lazy/tired to get up and walk three feet to my bookshelves and then spend an hour searching the books for moments. Honestly, I don’t recall many specific moments and more descriptions of Meera’s sister-ing of Jojen and also Bran. What I can think of is
- Meera and Jojen sort of snarking at each other at Queenscrown about how high the tower is and Jojen tells her there’s lots of trees back home that are taller and Meera goes on about how it feels taller because the tower is alone and the world feels so wide and I’m getting emotional.
- Meera always looking after Jojen, keeping him warm up north and crying over how Jojen is wasting away
- She takes Jojen fishing in the cave
- I think Howland purposefully sent both his children ITB but in the show it’s unclear why or how the Reeds went north to find Bran and it seems almost like they ran away and Meera followed to protect Jojen.
- I will always love that moment in 3x02 when Meera encapsulates her entire character with the “Some people will always need help, that doesn’t mean they’re not worth helping” line while looking at her boys.
